Package pl.polsl.lab.Model_package

Class ModelStatisticsSpotify

java.lang.Object
pl.polsl.lab.Model_package.ModelStatisticsSpotify
public class ModelStatisticsSpotify extends Object
This class represents the data model for Spotify statistics. It contains methods to read and process statistics data.
Version:
3.0
Author:
Piotr

      Returns:
      A List of Spotify statistics (ModelStatisticsSpotify).
      Throws:
      FileNotFoundException - If the specified file is not found.

    • saveDataToFile

      public void saveDataToFile(List<ModelStatisticsSpotify> spotifystatslist, String filePath)
      Saves data to a specified file path. This method takes a list of Spotify statistics and saves the data to a file located at the given file path.
      Parameters:
      spotifystatslist - A list of Spotify statistics to be saved.
      filePath - The path where the data will be stored.

    • mostPopularArtist

      public List<Map.Entry<String,Integer>> mostPopularArtist(List<ModelStatisticsSpotify> spotifystatslist)
      Finds the most popular artist(s) based on Spotify statistics. This method analyzes a list of Spotify statistics and identifies the artist(s) with the most plays.
      Parameters:
      spotifystatslist - A list of Spotify statistics to analyze.
      Returns:
      A list of `Map.Entry` containing the artist's name (as a string) and their total plays count.

    • setStatSpotify

      public List<ModelStatisticsSpotify> setStatSpotify(String reg, List<ModelStatisticsSpotify> list)
      Filters the list of Spotify statistics based on a specified region.
      Parameters:
      reg - The region to filter by. Pass "WorldWide" to include all regions.
      list - The list of Spotify statistics to filter.
      Returns:
      A list of Spotify statistics that belong to the specified region or the entire list if "WorldWide" is selected.
